#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This wiki is designed to be distributed and \"redundant\" (as in having "
"multiple copies). Basically, this is to allow you to access the "
"documentation even if the network goes down. This is done through "
"[[ikiwiki]], which is a the engine behind this wiki."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Basic offline editing and sharing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Basically, this wiki is a collection of [[ikiwiki/markdown]]-formatted pages "
"committed to a git repository. The git repository can be freely cloned using "
"this command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    git clone http://anarcat.ath.cx/software/mtl-mesh-wiki.git/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This will at least provide you with the raw source, the text files that "
"generate the wiki website. There you can make changes and send me the "
"patches by email."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a mirror"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"To create a mirror of this wiki, if it ever goes down, you can start from "
"the above repository and create a new wiki."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "The following steps should get you going:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    git clone --bare http://anarcat.ath.cx/software/mtl-mesh-wiki.git/\n"
"    git clone mtl-mesh-wiki.git\n"
"    cd mtl-mesh-wiki\n"
"    edit meta/mtl-mesh-wiki.setup # fix paths\n"
"    ikiwiki --setup meta/mtl-mesh-wiki.setup\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"See also [[meta/Maintenance]] for the plugins to enable and the hooks "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"(!) Oh, and [this](http://piny.be/jrayhawk/notes/ikiwiki_creation/)  may "
"also be of use if the above doesn't work."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Merging back into the wiki"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Now that multi-user configuration is enabled in the wiki (see "
"[[maintenance]]), i can allow git over SSH access for people that are into "
"that kind of stuff, just ask here or by email."
msgstr ""

